# FIX 10 ({{ sim_id }}-only) — de-duplicate the recorded video to one panel per camera.
# RoboCasa Kitchen's GrootRoboCasaEnv emits, for EACH of the 3 PandaOmron cameras (side_0,
# side_1, wrist_0), BOTH a processed res256 obs key AND a raw res512 copy
# (gymnasium_groot.py:112-115 `obs[mapped_name.replace("256","512")] = np.copy(...)`). The policy
# only ever consumes the res256 keys (rldx_policy.py:335-340,482-484); res512 is never an input.
# But VideoRecordingWrapper.step() hstacks EVERY obs key containing "video" (video_recording_
# wrapper.py:413), so the saved MP4 becomes a 6-panel 1536-wide strip — each camera shown twice
# (256 + 512). Narrow that collector to skip the res512 duplicates → a clean 3-panel strip, one
# view per camera, matching exactly what the policy sees. Other sims (GR-1/SIMPLER/LIBERO) have no
# res512 keys, so this is RoboCasa-Kitchen-only and a no-op elsewhere. Patches the runtime clone
# ONLY (vendoring-0 invariant); obs/policy/eval are untouched (video framing only → SR unaffected).
log "[5/8] FIX 10: de-duplicating recorded video (drop res512 panels, keep one per camera)..."
